{"questionId":"27718","questionHtml":"<p>Find the maximum time, in hours per week, that an employee can work and still be&nbsp;considered part-time.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not penalize for inclusion or non-inclusion of endpoints for probabilities using a normal distribution. For example, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>, etc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>recognition that probabilities sum to 1 (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>expressing the three regions in one variable&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>904</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>904</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>904</mn><mo>+</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math> correctly indicated on labelled bell diagram</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>904</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>904</mn><mo>+</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>expressing either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;only in terms of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>·</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>904</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>032</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>904</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>064</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>032</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>18167</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27718","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.9d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the maximum time, in hours per week, that an employee can work and still be considered part-time.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}